<item>
            <title>[PDFBOX-3108] Font cache is always rebuilt when font skipped</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-3108</link>
                <project id="12310760" key="PDFBOX">PDFBox</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If a font is skipped because of a missing name, the font is not added to the fontInfoList. This means that at the next program start, the list will be rebuilt.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This has happened for me all the time, I&apos;m just too patient so I didn&apos;t realize the problem. It happens with the attached font, which is on my system.&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;There should be a type of entry in the cache file that mentions a file, but no font name, so that the next time the font directories are looked into, that file is not considered to be a new font.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
